  "informal_statement": "min(a,b) + max(a,b) = a + b -- the classic min/max complementary identity.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Case split on a <= b or b <= a. In each case, min and max resolve to a or b explicitly (min_eq_left/min_eq_right, max_eq_left/max_eq_right), reducing the goal to a trivial sum equality.",
