  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 5c58440d), kernel_verified on the second attempt. The domain's existing min/max family (`avg_between_min_max`, `min_add_min_le`, `max_add_le`) are all strict INEQUALITIES; this adds the exact complementary EQUALITY, min(a,b)+max(a,b)=a+b, confirmed via `mathlib_search_declarations` (no `min_add_max`/`max_add_min` hits) and grep of the packet corpus to have no prior duplicate. First attempt used bare `simp [min_eq_left h, max_eq_right h]` for both branches, which left a trivial `b + a = a + b` unsolved in the second branch (simp didn't auto-apply commutativity here) -- fixed by using `rw` instead of `simp` and appending `ring` to close the residual commutativity goal in that branch.",
